Properties.PropertyValue: Submitting a CAR will send an Email to the Assigned Person and the CAR manager, and OPEN the CAR.
When you are finished with your work, push the SEND FOR REVIEW button

One method to perform a Root Cause Analysis is to ask the question Why? five times, starting with Why did the discrepancy happen Ex. Why was the cover not sewn per the pattern? Another method to perform a Root Cause Analysis is to fill out a Fish Bone Diagram See QA-F-017 in the AS9100 vault in Meridian

Any actions done to contain the problem should be listed in this section. Example of Containment actions. All stock and in-transit product will be verified. The part will be put on hold in Epicor to hold shipments. All inventory will been quarantined and will be reviewed by Quality. Once the Containment Actions are complete, the comments section should be updated with the findings/results. The Corrective Action should immediately fix the problem in order to prevent any more escapes. Example of Corrective Action. A Quality Alert will be posted to ensure all are aware of the discrepancy. Parts will be reworked to meet the drawing

The Follow Up must review the Preventive and Corrective Actions to ensure they were effective. Ex. No more rejections have occurred since the implementation of the Preventive Action. All evidence of the implementation of the Corrective and Preventive Actions must be verified and attached to the CAR. Ex. Training documentation of a new/updated procedure needs to be attached

The Preventive Action should directly answer the question What needs to be done to ensure the discrepancy does not happen again?. Example of Preventive Action. An ECR will be generated for this part, and all similar parts, to update the manufacturing documents. The procedure will be updated and all relating departments will be trained on the new procedure
